            Beyond Testing: Creating Supportive Work Environments
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Workplace substance abuse is a significant concern affecting employee health, safety, productivity, 
            and the overall work environment. While drug testing programs are an important component of 
            addressing substance abuse in the workplace, employers have a much broader role to play in 
            prevention. Creating a comprehensive approach that focuses on education, supportive policies, 
            and a healthy workplace culture can significantly reduce substance abuse issues while promoting 
            employee wellbeing.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            This article explores how employers can develop proactive strategies beyond testing to prevent 
            workplace substance abuse, support affected employees, and foster a healthier, more productive 
            work environment.
          </p>
  
          <!-- The Business Impact Section -->
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2"
