            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              Balancing confidentiality with safety requirements
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              Recognizing addiction as a medical condition that may qualify for certain accommodations
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              Consulting with legal counsel to ensure policies comply with labor laws
            </li>
          </ul>
  
          <!-- Implementing an Effective Program Section -->
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2"
          >
            Implementing an Effective Program
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            For companies looking to develop or enhance their prevention efforts, consider these 
            implementation steps:
          </p>
  
          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-8 space-y-3">
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Assess current needs and existing resources</strong> - 
              Understand the specific substance abuse risks in your industry and workplace
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Develop a written policy with stakeholder input</strong> - 
              Include HR, legal, safety personnel, and employee representatives
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Communicate the policy clearly</strong> - 
              Ensure all employees understand both the rules and the resources available
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Train supervisors and managers</strong> - 
              Provide skills needed to recognize issues and respond appropriately
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Establish or enhance EAP services</strong> - 
              Ensure these services are accessible and confidential
            </li>
            <li class="leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Monitor, evaluate, and adjust</strong> - 
              Regularly review program effectiveness and make improvements
            </li>
          </ol>
  
          <!-- Conclusion Section -->
          <h2
            class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 border-b-2 border-blue-500 pb-2"
          >
            Conclusion
          </h2>
          <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Employers have a unique opportunity to play a pivotal role in preventing workplace substance 
            abuse and supporting employee wellness. While drug testing is one important component, truly 
            effective prevention requires a comprehensive approach that addresses workplace culture, 
            provides education and support resources, and balances accountability with compassion.
          </p>
          <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
            By implementing these strategies, employers not only reduce the risks and costs associated 
            with workplace substance abuse but also create healthier, more supportive work environments 
            where all employees can thrive. The investment in prevention and support programs typically 
            yields significant returns in terms of improved productivity, reduced accidents and absenteeism, 
            and a more positive workplace culture.
          </p>
